{
  "texts": [
    "However, these interactions are usually short and might not capture the entire activity.",
    "Indeed, the subject may move to another location to take medicines, such as a dining room or kitchen, where other activities are usually performed.",
    "Finally, the misclassifications of entering home and leaving home are due to an insufficient sensing infrastructure to recognize these activities (i.e., no magnetic sensor on the main door).",
    "For instance, when a subject leaves home starting from the kitchen, ADL-LLM sometimes mislabels it as meal preparation, while windows only including movements in the hall lead to label leaving home as entering home due to LLM's assumptions about the home entry points.Finally, Figure 8 shows the Empirical Cumulative Density Function (ECDF) of the response times provided by gpt-3.5 on both datasets.",
    "We observe that ≈ 80% of the responses are generated within 2 seconds, and almost all responses for both datasets are generated within four seconds."
  ]
}